Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Event>
    public class Event
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Event>
    An Event is created whenever a state change occurs within the queue. Events help keep track of time and have a log of the state of each Customer within the queue at that particular time.

      • Event

        public Event​(java.util.PriorityQueue<Customer> myQueue,
             boolean isArrivalLog)
        An Arrival Event is created with a queue of customers representing arrivals. This constructor exists to handle the arrival logs of level 4.
        Parameters:
        myQueue - the priority queue of arrived customers
        isArrivalLog - for level 4 of the project, whereby the arrivals have to be printed.

      • Event

        public Event​(Customer currentCustomer,
             java.util.PriorityQueue<Customer> remainingQueue)
        An event is created whenever there's a change of Customer's state.
        Parameters:
        currentCustomer - A customer's action/state change generates an event and this is the customer currently looked at
        remainingQueue - the rest of the priority queue of customers other than the currently looked at customer
